result.name: Dan Ryan's Chicago Grill

reviews.text:
Classic American dishes in a sport bar and pub setting.

American fares such as burgers, ribs, steaks and sandwiches. Brunch options and big breakfasts are also available. Portion is generous and food generally well executed. The complimentary warm breadbasket is awesome. 

Atmosphere is chill and children friendly. It's a good place to hangout for the super bowl and major sporting events. The bar section is also good for a quick after work drink. Service is prompt and very friendly.

Good family diner.

Excellent service 
We are regular clientele of Dan Ryan's at Ocean Terminal due to its food and good service. We went there for dinner this evening, the food was good as usual. However, the service was exceptional. Special thanks to Fisher Ng who served us, bravo to the exceptional service. Special thanks also to the manager, Helen, who was the model and leader of an exceptional team. We will be back 😊

Typical Amercian cuisine with big portions for Asians.  Many choices other than burger and salad and the pricing is reasonable.  Deco is nice and service is good.  Be prepared to have kids around, and just located next to the escalator.
Solid service from the wait staff and helpful greeters. Portions are large (read, American size), which makes it good value for money.

The food and service was great at this location and we would have given then a much higher rating, however, beware of how they post foreign credit/debit card amounts.  When we paid our bill and they processed our credit card, we chose local currency and the original amount was posted that way on our bank statement.  A few days later our bank statement shows that the amount was reversed and then reposted in the Canadian currency amount which is a higher amount.  I contacted our bank and they advised this was all requested by Dan Ryan's.  So I emailed Dan Ryan's to ask them what was going on and to have the amounts corrected.  I never had a reply from them nor did they try to contact me in any was.  This is extremely frustrating!  When the option is given abroad we always choose local currency and not our Canadian currency and I sent them the paperwork to prove it.  Not good service!
